correctness.rationale: Significant factual and schema issues. Correct items include: precursor Zn(Cppm)2, substrate Si(100), carrier/purge Ar, 200 °C, O2 plasma power 100 W (for pO/WpO), purge time 15 s, GPCs (~0.13/0.07/0.10 nm/cycle), cycles (200/350/270), film thicknesses (28.3/24.6/27.7 nm), and no nucleation delay. Major problems: (1) ALD method mis-specified: processes using O2 plasma (pO, WpO) are labeled TALD but should be PEALD; plasma power is inappropriately included for the H2O-only (W) thermal process. (2) Dosing for WpO misses the separate O2 plasma exposure time (8 s); only H2O (15 s) is shown. (3) Reactor pressure (20 mmHg) is not reported in the article—value appears fabricated. (4) Flow rates are not given in the article—values appear fabricated. (5) Many material/device properties are fabricated or inconsistent: optical (RI, absorption, bandgap, UV-Vis), electrical (resistivity, carrier density, mobility, Hall), uniformity, conformality, roughness (AFM), device metrics (μFE, VTH, SS, on/off), and safety/reproducibility—none are reported. Film density given as 5.6 g/cm3 (XRR) contradicts article (~5.1–5.2 g/cm3 via HR-RBS) and uses an unallowed unit. (6) Schema violations: growth-per-cycle unit should be ANGSTROM (Å) but NanoM is used; dosing/purge time units must be MilliSEC but SEC is used; absorptionCoefficient unit not in schema (provided PER-CentiM); filmDensity unit should be GM-PER-DeciM3 per schema but GM-PER-CentiM3 is used. (7) Elemental concentration (50% by XPS) is not reported. To improve, correct ALD methods (PEALD for pO and WpO), remove plasmaPower for W, add explicit O2 plasma dose for WpO (8 s), remove or mark unknown values not in the article (pressure, flow, optical/electrical/device/uniformity/conformality/roughness), fix GPC units to Å, change time units to MilliSEC, align film density and method with the article (≈5.1–5.2 g/cm3 from HR-RBS), and ensure all values are traceable to the source.

completeness.rationale: The three distinct processes (O2 plasma, H2O, H2O→O2 plasma) are identified and several key parameters (200 °C, Ar purge/carrier, 15 s purge, 16 s precursor dose, cycle counts, GPCs, thicknesses) match the article. However, the extraction contains multiple schema violations, many untraceable/fabricated values, and some incorrect assignments: (1) Schema/unit errors: growthPerCycle reported in nm instead of ANGSTROM; dosingTime/purgeTime units use SEC instead of required MilliSEC; absorptionCoefficient unit PER-CentiM not allowed (schema expects UNITLESS); filmDensity unit GM-PER-CentiM3 not allowed (schema expects GM-PER-DeciM3). (2) Method inconsistencies: aldMethod is set to TALD for all processes; pO and WpO should be PEALD; plasmaPower is incorrectly provided for the thermal H2O-only process. (3) Missing/incorrect dosing for WpO: the O2 plasma step (8 s) is not included in dosingTime; purge sequencing for the second oxidant is not represented. (4) Untraceable/fabricated parameters: reactor pressure (20 mTorr), all flow rates, optical properties (n, absorption), electrical properties, device properties, uniformity, conformality, roughness, and the film density value/method (5.6 g/cm3, XRR) are not reported in the article; film density in the paper is ~5.1–5.2 g/cm3 derived from HR-RBS/ellipsometry. (5) Film composition method mismatch: elemental concentration is labeled XPS with 50% while the article uses HR-RBS and reports O/Zn ≈ 1; method should reflect RBS. (6) Delivery method is marked “Not specified” though the article states a bubbler at 70 °C. (7) Duplicate filmThickness entries appear both inside thicknessControl and at processParameters level. These issues collectively make the extraction largely non-compliant and not fully traceable to the source text.
